<para id="import-auto-id1169738151626">Think about the drinking bird at the beginning of this section (<link target-id="import-auto-id1169738209561"/>). Although the bird enjoys the theoretical maximum efficiency possible, if left to its own devices over time, the bird will cease “drinking.” What are some of the dissipative processes that might cause the bird’s motion to cease?</para>
